				"string" : "## 2. **Learning Unit 1 Expansion**\n\n* Expand LU1 as a **tree of pages**.\n* Decide on naming of:\n  *Units, Steps, Side Roads, Main Path*.\n* Represent as:\n\n  * One main path (beginner progression)\n  * Multiple side-roads (deep dives, tools)\n* Generate a **visual learning map** using Scenery.\n\n## 3. **GT Core Concepts vs Technical Side Issues**\n\n* Extract the essential “What is GT?” points:\n\n  * GT as an environment for *explainable systems*\n  * Case study as anchor\n  * Domain modelling + live exploration\n  * Lepiter + playgrounds\n  * Creating contextual tools (views, actions, searches)\n  * Side roads:\n\n    * Language workbenches\n    * Mondrian\n    * Sceneries\n    * Examples\n\n## 4. **Patterns**\n\n* Accordion metaphor as a formal pattern:\n\n  * Inspect → code → dive → extract methods → return\n* Need a **tutorial use case** (TG provided Slack pointers).\n\n## 5. **Wardley Mapping for GT Newcomers**\n\nCreate a Wardley Map including:\n\n* User needs (Newcomers)\n* Value chain:\n\n  * GT Book\n  * Personal KB / Lepiter\n  * MD IDE & coding tools\n  * Bloc GUI\n  * EDD (Example Driven Development)\n  * MD methodology\n  * GitHub + OS (commodities)\n* Identify evolution stages for each.\n\n## 6. **Lower-priority pages**\n\n* **Gentle Intro to ST** improvement based on Discord feedback.\n* Add *Design Principles Behind Smalltalk* to History.\n* Recycle / adapt **zeniko**’s GT descriptions.\n* **Mondrian tutorial**:\n\n  * Finding elements\n  * Prototyping & layout changes\n  * Tooltips\n  * Extracting methods\n  * Parametrizing selection\n  * Exporting as PNG\n* **TreePager demo page**:\n\n  * Based on Discord examples (Nov 15–17, 2025)\n"
